frameDefinitions: An Authority excuses an Offense that an Offender has committed, with the effect of ending or preventing any punishment.
This frame describes a complex event which lasts some amount of time, consisting of a beginning stage, a stage where the process is ongoing, and a finish or end.
An Agent has done or omitted to do an Act or is responsible for the obtaining of a State_of_affairs, which a Judge deems to constitute a violation of an obligation or a moral guideline.
In this frame, an Authority allows a Protagonist to know (in some way) that they may or may not engage in an Action.
A Judge refrains from imposing, or demanding a punishment for an Evaluee who has committed an Offense.
